se.softhouse.common.strings

Interface Describable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Command, Describables.SerializableDescription

    @Immutable
public interface Describable
    Allows for lazily created descriptions (i.e Strings) and the possible performance optimization that the string is not constructed if it's not used. If you already have a created String it's recommended to just use that instead. This interface is typically implemented using an anonymous class.
    See Also:
